OL,3,C'Mortgage prisoner' forced to move
OL,4,Cback in with parents at 42
OL,6,FA woman who was forced to sell her
OL,7,Fhome and move back in with her parents
OL,8,Fin her 40s after being trapped in a
OL,9,Fhigh interest mortgage is backing
OL,10,Fcalls for Government action.
OL,12,FKeely Wray, 42, from had to sell her
OL,13,Fhome last year despite having worked
OL,14,Ftwo jobs for more than 16 years to try
OL,15,Fto keep up with the payments.
OL,17,FShe is one of thousands of so-called
OL,18,F"mortgage prisoners" who were left
OL,19,Ftied into high-interest mortgages
OL,20,Fafter their lenders collapse during
OL,21,Fthe 2008 financial crisis.
