OL,3,C'Mortgage prisoner' forced to move
OL,4,Cback in with parents at 42
OL,6,FHe took out a 125% mortgage to
OL,7,Frenovate his family home a few weeks
OL,8,Fbefore the financial collapse and has
OL,9,Fsince been stuck paying inflated
OL,10,Fmonthly prices.
OL,12,FMr Poynton and his wife both lost
OL,13,Ftheir jobs during the crash and, as
OL,14,Fhouse prices plunged, their home went
OL,15,Finto negative equity.
OL,17,FThe stress led to separation and Mr
OL,18,FPoynton's wife suffered from
OL,19,Fdepression before her death in 2022.
