OL,6,FShe added: "People have felt there is
OL,7,Fnowhere to turn to. People have
OL,8,Fknocked on the door of the government,
OL,9,Fknocked on the door of Financial
OL,10,FConduct Authority (FCA) but so far
OL,11,Fnothing has been put in place which
OL,12,Factually alleviates the pressure on
OL,13,Fpeople."
OL,15,FA Treasury spokesperson said: "The
OL,16,FGovernment understands the
OL,17,Fdifficulties faced by borrowers who
OL,18,Fwere not able to switch to a new
OL,19,Fmortgage deal.
